<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="616" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2704</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-07">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 3 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Danish Merchants’ Guild representative here has asked Guild not to
                                submit further applications for dried fruit import permits owing to
                                excessive importations over ration allotted by British Government;
                                consequently not probable that further dried fruit shipments will be
                                allowed in Denmark until end this year.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>